    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "I see. But wouldn't telling my students to view it as \"historical evolution\" instead of \"judicial activism\" be a bit biased? If the argument is that judges are essentially bypassing the democratic process to implement their own social values, isn't that a valid constitutional concern rather than just a matter of perspective? How do I teach this without telling them which side is 'correct'?",
